 <h2><U>Soling the Plane of Innovation</U></h2><br><br>The Plane of Innovation is a decent exp zone, and the money can be good solo. Definately one of the better cash spots for solo exp hunting.<br><br>However, it can be reasonably risky when you get an add, especially before you get Rathes Son - and thus the breakin can be tricky and hunting can be risky.<br><br><br>Simply walk around killing, and turn back when your no longer beating the spawns. Time it so your only venturing as deep as you need to in order to have enough mobs. No point in venturing deeper than needed, as it gets riskier and further from zone.<br><br><br>Avoid the factory - your better off hunting whatever yard trash you can find.<br><br><br><br></center><b><u>Zone Information:</u></b><br><br><a href='http://www.eqmages.com' onClick='moblist(160); return false;'>Plane of Innovation (PoI) mob list</a><br>
<a href='http://www.eqmages.com' onClick='questlist(160); return false;'>Plane of Innovation (PoI) quest list</a><br><br><b><u>Comments/Feedback:</u></b><br><br><i><b>Eandori Raintree</b> says:</i><br>Adds can happen pretty frequently, mobs can train by you due to the narrow zone paths, and many mobs hit harder then they should for good exp/balance.  I would highly recommend Plane of Disease soloing over Innovation.<br><br><i><b>Naresha Qysilthilas</b> says:</i><br>Soloing PoInnovation is not a really good idea. The mobs hit too hard to be really exp efficient. Avoid archaic models if your pet can't handle the normal obsoletes without heals. Archaics hit hard and summon. I usually have to summon Servant of Ro and Host of the Elements when I encounter one solo. Duoing is much easier, especially if you can chain pet with another pet class.<br><br><i><b>Naresha Qysilthilas</b> says:</i><br>Also if possible go left instead of right when you first zone in. Mob density is higher to your right. The first pull is a double mob pull most of the time. Also watch for roaming erratic models, there is 1 - 2 roamers for either path up at any time unless already killed. If you are soloing the spawn catches up with you fast regardless of how powerful or buffed you are. Be ready to gate or train to zone in after about 20 mobs.<br><br><i><b>Drauss</b> says:</i><br>I wouldnt try soloing in Plane of Innovation. It really to much of a pain for the exp. If your 64/65 soloing isnt the best thing to do. I would hit up Plane of Valor or BoT and get a group for some faster and more exp kills.<br><br><i><b>Farrudar</b> says:</i><br>Instead of using Rathe's Son I use Wind of Xegony.  My pet focus is GoDs and with max crit and max flurry GOD AA the air pet obliterates the mobs.  You can tank more than one if you get adds so long as you use both the 64 and 54 heal spell.<br><br><i><b>merloo</b> says:</i><br>i find that i can  single pull with malaise about 90% of the time. but  i was wondering how can a mage solo here without a slower, these mobs hit way to hard. i could be wrong and probably am but thats my 2 cents worth<br><br><i><b>Sar</b> says:</i><br>I've solo'd in PoI many a times, just use firebolt of tallon and make sure your pets ready ( i use ward of xegony ) and have at um, single of course...if pet gets down to low he'll enrage and you can finish with nukes anyways<br><br><form action='rate.php' method='post' name='rate'>
